## Git Commands

### Undoing Changes

```bash
# Unstage files
git reset HEAD file.ts

# Discard local changes
git checkout -- file.ts

# Undo last commit (keep changes)
git reset --soft HEAD~1

# Undo last commit (discard changes)
git reset --hard HEAD~1

# Revert a commit (creates new commit)
git revert <commit-hash>
```

### Stashing

```bash
# Save current changes
git stash

# List stashes
git stash list

# Apply stash
git stash apply
git stash pop  # Apply and remove

# Drop stash
git stash drop
```

### Branch Management

```bash
# List branches
git branch
git branch -a  # All branches including remote

# Delete branch
git branch -d feature/old-feature
git push origin --delete feature/old-feature

# Rename branch
git branch -m old-name new-name
```

## Collaboration

### Rebasing

```bash
# Interactive rebase
git rebase -i HEAD~3

# Rebase feature branch onto main
git checkout feature/my-feature
git rebase main

# If conflicts, resolve and continue
git rebase --continue
```

### Conflict Resolution

```bash
# When conflict occurs
git status  # See conflicted files

# Edit files to resolve conflicts
# Look for <<<<<<< HEAD markers

# After resolving
git add resolved-file.ts
git commit  # or git rebase --continue
```

## GitHub Actions (Basic)

### Workflow Example

```yaml
# .github/workflows/ci.yml
name: CI

on:
  push:
    branches: [main, develop]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

jobs:
  test:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v3
      - uses: actions/setup-node@v3
        with:
          node-version: '18'
      - run: npm install
      - run: npm test
      - run: npm run lint
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Commit Often

Make small, logical commits rather than large ones.

### 2. Write Good Commit Messages

Follow conventional commits format.

### 3. Keep Branches Up to Date

Regularly merge/rebase from main branch.

### 4. Review Before Push

```bash
# Check what will be pushed
git log origin/main..HEAD

# Review diff
git diff origin/main
```

### 5. Use .gitignore

```gitignore
# Dependencies
node_modules/
__pycache__/

# Environment variables
.env
.env.local

# Build outputs
dist/
build/
.next/

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
```

## Checklist for Git Workflow

Before committing:

- [ ] Code follows project style guidelines
- [ ] Tests pass locally
- [ ] No debugging code left in
- [ ] Commit message follows convention
- [ ] Related files committed together
- [ ] .gitignore updated if needed
- [ ] Large files not committed (use Git LFS if needed)

Before pushing:

- [ ] Branch is up to date with main
- [ ] All commits have descriptive messages
- [ ] No sensitive data in commits (API keys, passwords)
- [ ] Changes are tested

Before PR:

- [ ] PR title is clear and descriptive
- [ ] PR description explains changes
- [ ] All CI checks pass
- [ ] Code reviewed by yourself
- [ ] Related issues linked
